{{Infobox noble | name = Kushiukanushi no Mikoto | image = | image_size = | caption = | era = [[Kofun period]] | birth_date = Unknown | death_date = Unknown | other_names = Sagayuushi no Mikoto, Nakatomi no Muraji no Sagayuushi | honorary_title = | deity_name = | posthumous_name = | burial_place = | Rank = | lord = [[Emperor Suinin]] | clan = {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|12=draft}} | parents = Father: {{ill|Kamikikatsu no Mikoto|ja|神聞勝命|12=draft}} | children = {{ill|Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto|ja|国摩大鹿島命|12=draft}} }}
'''Kushiukanushi no Mikoto''' (久志宇賀主命) was an ancient Japanese noble and an ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|12=draft}}.
== Overview == In the *{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}*, during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|12=draft}}, an entry in the 26th year of the emperor’s reign notes that the emperor consulted Kushiukanushi no Mikoto (referred to as the ancestor of the Nakatomi clan) about whom should conduct the worship of {{ill|Ōyamato no Ōkami|ja|倭大国魂神|12=draft}}. The divination revealed that {{ill|Nunakiiri-hime no Mikoto|ja|渟名城入姫命|12=draft}} was the most suitable for this role.
== Genealogy == Kushiukanushi no Mikoto is identified as the son of {{ill|Kamikikatsu no Mikoto|ja|神聞勝命|12=draft}} and the father of {{ill|Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto|ja|国摩大鹿島命|12=draft}} according to genealogical records.<ref>『{{ill|Sonpi Bunmyaku|ja|尊卑分脈|12=draft}}』</ref>
